      'Driving in California is not a right — it is a privilege. That distinction matters. A right cannot easily be taken away from you. A privilege can be suspended or revoked if you abuse it. Your California driver\'s license represents a legal agreement between you and the state: California gives you the privilege of driving, and in return, you agree to follow the rules of the road.',
